{
  "doc_id": "824",
  "text": "Although Doxil has been FDA-approved for multiple indications, several questions remain over the mechanism of action [CITATION_1] . Here we focus on the kinetics of doxorubicin leakage from Doxil liposomes. Previous studies reported the amount of doxorubicin leaked out of liposomes at one or two time points, and hence provide useful comparisons, but do not provide details of the kinetics [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Here we consider three processes: doxorubicin dissolution, ionization, and transport across the liposome lipid bilayer.",
